@Pani Korunova I don't think Sarah's comment has to do with intelligence and abilities but with readiness. As in prep time. I don't think I could have solved this one without lookups after my first decade of solving, for example. I doubt that being able to crack it now when I could not have done so then depended on any increase in my intelligence or even on very much increased knowledge of language, but on gradually developing more strategies for triggering my own latent knowledge. 

Developing "readiness" for these seems to be an ongoing process. This community we are both in has a sizable cohort of decades-long solvers alongside a sizable cohort of newbies. Most newbies should at least occasionally find a Monday at their level of readiness, and most oldies should at least occasionally find a Saturday at theirs. I know that means that at times there will be a Thursday or Saturday that I just don't get and that feels unfair, because I'm far from the most accomplished solver here.

May there be many puzzles that hit the sweet spot for you!

